001package com.technototes.library.hardware;
002
003import com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.HardwareDevice;
004
005/**
006 * This isn't worth actually doing. You have to redo your configuration constantly if you create
007 * a device that isn't part of the core runtime :(
008 *
009 * @param <T> The type of the device
010 */
011@Deprecated
012public class DummyDevice<T> implements HardwareDevice {
013
014    private final T internal;
015
016    public DummyDevice(T inter) {
017        internal = inter;
018    }
019
020    @Override
021    public Manufacturer getManufacturer() {
022        return Manufacturer.Unknown;
023    }
024
025    @Override
026    public String getDeviceName() {
027        return internal.toString();
028    }
029
030    @Override
031    public String getConnectionInfo() {
032        return "dummy device";
033    }
034
035    @Override
036    public int getVersion() {
037        return 0;
038    }
039
040    @Override
041    public void resetDeviceConfigurationForOpMode() {}
042
043    @Override
044    public void close() {}
045
046    public T get() {
047        return internal;
048    }
049}
